race.comment: THAT A BOY (4) found Rosehill too tough but was quickly back on track when winning a 58 easily here over this trip. He maps well and keeps improving. The local has some weight relief and can go back-to-back. COSMIC RIDE (9) got too far back at Cootamundra as favourite but his Canberra form prior reads well for this. She's capable of riding the speed and also carries less. A solid each-way play. WIN THE DAY (3) is a third-up winner and will find this more suitable than Rosehill. Has an awkward gate but she has more to give and is ready to fire. MAH ALI (2) went close in a 75 at Canberra three back and has been racing in strong provincial contests since. Much better placed today and the 3kg claim brings her right into it.
